cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is primarily focused on the application of Deep Reinforcement Learning (RL) algorithms to eliminate sub-optimal actions in text-based games. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. Additionally, the paper also involves the use of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) techniques to train the Action Elimination Network (AEN) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) to process the text-based games. The paper also involves the use of Neural Networks (cs.NE) to implement the AE-DQN architecture and Robotics (cs.RO) to apply the proposed method to real-world scenarios.
